Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Caroline Yan

2023-03-13

My meme

My meme is of a couple having a disagreement, where the girlfriend is telling her boyfriend to stop playing a song called wonderwall, which he replies with “i said maybe”, which is a lyric of the song— I wanted to recreate this meme and spice it up because of my love for the song, and my sister constantly telling me to stop singing it.

library(magick)

### Creating my meme with the couple with their text
girlfriend <- image_read("https://i.postimg.cc/VknXHGx0/chadettewhbkg.png") %>%
  image_scale(300) %>%
  image_flop %>%
  image_annotate(text = "babe, could you please\nstop playing wonderwall",
                 color = "#000000",
                 boxcolor = "grey",
                 size = 22,
                 font = "Georgia",
                 gravity = "north")

boyfriend <- image_read("https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/74567163?v=4") %>%
  image_scale(330) %>%
  image_fill(color= "transparent") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "i said maybe",
                 color = "#000000",
                 boxcolor = "grey",
                 size = 23,
                 font = "Georgia",
                 gravity = "west") 

### Adding the Oasis Album Cover and Guitar
album <- image_read("https://i.scdn.co/image/ab67616d0000b27385e5dcc05cc216a10f141480") %>%
  image_scale(350)

guitar <- image_read("https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/guitar-drawing-vector-image-illustration-53937587.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(290) 

### Adding a White Box 
white_box <- image_blank(width = 300,
                         height = 300,
                         color = "#ffffff")

### Layering the boyfriend with the album cover
glory <- c(album, boyfriend)
glory <- image_scale(glory, "300x300")
image_mosaic(glory) 

### Combining them together  
winding_vector <- c(girlfriend, image_mosaic(glory))
top_row <- image_append(winding_vector)

oasis_vector <- c(white_box, guitar)
bottom_row <- image_append(oasis_vector)

c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(600)

meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack=TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(600)

### Saving my meme
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

My GIF shows four frames, starting from the character Eric Cartman’s room, the outside of his home, his bus stop, then the University of Auckland, which is a representation of my daily routine from Monday to Friday, hence the annotation “This is my life”.

library(magick)

### Creating 4 frames for my background
frame1 <- image_read("https://i.quotev.com/2a3xd54waaaa.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)
frame2 <- image_read("https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/southpark/images/b/be/CartmanResidence.png/revision/latest?cb=20200115195026") %>%
  image_scale(300)
frame3 <- image_read("https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/southpark/images/c/ca/Bus-stop.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20141214163925") %>%
  image_scale(300)
frame4 <- image_read("https://studyportals-cdn2.imgix.net/5cdb3c830c9fc.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

### Combining the frames
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4) %>%
  image_resize('400x250!') %>%
  image_morph() 

### Animating and Annotating it
animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 10) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "This is my life", size = 35, gravity = "north")

print(animation)

### Saving the GIF
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
